Tutorial: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PFP0oXNNveg
Tutorial for Angular to Rest: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KhzGSHNhnbI

Mongodb:
- Installed
- C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.0\bin\Mongo
- Create db - use tasklist
- Create collection - db.createCollection("tasks")
- Add documents - tasklist.tasks.insert({ title: 'Call Fotiana',   state: 'Done' })
- List all: use tasklist
            db.tasks.find({})
- Delete one: db.tasks.deleteOne( { _id: "5" } )

Angular - followed angular.io quickstart guide in client folder

Postman test:
    Post: Body / Raw / JSON: 
    {
        "title": "Call Chrystalla",
        "state": "To Do"
    }
    Delete: http://localhost:3000/api/task/5b40ac73ae6985250109c499

Run server: node server  (or run nodemon to auto update)

Create new Angular project: ng new client
Run Angular project: ng serve --open